MY MEME FILE

The meme is about two different emotions saying “I LOVE STATS”.

library(magick)
#first meme
cat<-image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/038/374/cover2.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("1000x500!")
#second meme
sad<-image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/034/772/Untitled-1.png")%>%
  image_resize("1000x500!")

work<-image_blank(width = 500,
                  height = 500,
                  color = "#000000")%>%
  image_annotate(text="I LOVE STATS",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 100,
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#append the meme together
left<-image_append(c (work,cat))
right<-image_append(c(work,sad))

new_meme<-c(left,right)%>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>%
  image_scale(800)

# save image
image_write(new_meme, "myMeme.png")

MY ANIMATION GIF

# Load required library
library(magick)

# Load images
cat <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/038/374/cover2.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("1000x500!")
sad <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/034/772/Untitled-1.png") %>%
  image_resize("1000x500!")

# Create frames for animation
frame1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I LOVE STATS", color = "#FFFFFF", size = 50, font = "impact", gravity = "center")
frame2 <- frame1 %>%
  image_composite(image = cat, offset = "+50+100")
frame3 <- frame1 %>%
  image_composite(image = sad, offset = "+50+100")
frame4 <- frame1 %>%
  image_composite(image = cat, offset = "+150+50") %>%
  image_composite(image = sad, offset = "-150+200")

# Combine frames into an animation
animation <- image_join(c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>%
  image_scale(800) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 4)

# Save animation as a GIF file
image_write(animation, path = "my_animation.gif")
